    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-06-02T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-06-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="365"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d365">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">812.00/15134½</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Wilson</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-06-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">2 June, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: Here is the Mexican statement
                    recast in a way which I hope meets entirely the views you expressed
                        yesterday.<note n="4" xml:id="d365fn1">For the statement as issued, see <ref
                            target="frus1915#pg_694">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1915, p. 694</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>If it meets with your approval, will you not be kind enough to let Tumulty know
                    by telephone so that he may release it for the afternoon papers? I rather led
                    them to expect it yesterday when I saw them.</p>
                <p>And will you not see that correct copies are sent (they can be sent plain in the
                    circumstances) to our several representatives near the principal factional
                    chiefs, so that this may serve as a direct and personal reminder.</p>
                <p>Cordially and faithfully,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>W. W.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
